MangoHub: Master Product Specification
MangoHub is a unified, multi-service digital marketplace designed to bridge the gap between daily commerce, lifestyle services, and secure fintech. By integrating shopping, hospitality, real estate, event ticketing, and instant mobile payments into a single platform, MangoHub eliminates the friction of switching between multiple apps.

1. Core Marketplace Ecosystem
MangoHub operates as a multi-tenant platform where distinct business verticals coexist under a unified user experience.

A. Retail & E-Commerce (Shops)
Seller Frontends: Vendors can register, create a digital storefront, and self-manage their product catalogs.

Direct Purchases: Customers browse, add items to a universal cart, and checkout directly inside the app.

B. Real Estate (Verified Agents Only)
Scam Prevention: To ensure user safety and marketplace integrity, anonymous postings are strictly forbidden. Only verified agents and authenticated property owners can list assets for sale or rent.

Premium Discoverability: Properties are listed with baseline descriptions, photos, and general areas, while keeping precise location data gated.

C. Event Ticketing
Ticket Management: Organizers can create events, set tiered pricing (e.g., General, VIP), and issue digital tickets directly to buyers.

App-Native Validation: Organizers use an embedded camera scanner inside the MangoHub app to validate entries at the door.

D. Hospitality & Lodging
Direct Bookings: Lodge, hotel, and short-term rental owners list available rooms directly on the platform.

Live Room Calendars: Every listing includes an automated, real-time availability calendar. This calendar dynamically blocks out dates, tracking all bookings made exclusively through the MangoHub ecosystem to prevent double-bookings.

2. Smart Escrow & Transaction Verification Workflow
To establish absolute trust in digital transactions, MangoHub routes all payments (excluding non-refundable fees) through a secure, platform-managed Escrow System. Funds are safely held by MangoHub and are only released when strict real-world milestones are verified through the app.

Retail/Shop Workflows
[Customer Pays] ──> [Funds Held in Escrow] ──> [Rider/Seller Delivers] ──> [Customer Gives Delivery Code] ──> [Seller Enters Code] ──> [Funds Released]
Customer purchases an item (e.g., clothing or electronics).

Funds are immediately locked in escrow.

Upon delivery, the rider or shop owner requests the Unique Delivery Code generated on the customer's app.

The transaction is marked complete only when the seller or delivery rider inputs this customer-provided code into the app.

Funds are instantly released to the vendor.

Event Ticket Workflows
Customer purchases a digital event ticket.

Revenue is securely held by MangoHub.

At the venue entry point, the customer presents their digital ticket.

An authorized event organizer scans the ticket using the MangoHub app scanner.

The system registers the check-in event, which automatically triggers the immediate release of those ticket funds to the organizer.

Lodge & Booking Workflows
Customer books a room and pays through the platform.

Funds are held securely in escrow.

Upon arrival at the lodge, the customer presents a booking-specific QR code generated by the app.

The lodge owner scans this QR code using the MangoHub app scanner to authorize the check-in.

The check-in registration triggers the release of the booking payment to the lodge owner's account.

Property Viewing Workflows
To combat time-wasting and unauthorized trespassing, exact property locations are hidden behind a Viewing Fee.

The user pays the required viewing fee.

Instant Instant Unlocks: The moment payment clears, the app instantly reveals:

The precise GPS route and interactive map navigation directing the user straight to the property.

The verified agent's or property owner's direct contact information.

The platform tool to officially schedule the physical visit.

Once these details are successfully unlocked, the transaction processes and the fee is released to the property owner.

3. Financial Infrastructure & Refund Architecture
Payment Gateway Integration
All monetary operations on MangoHub are powered natively by Paychangu, ensuring rapid processing and local compliance.

Mobile Money (Live): Complete integration with TNM Mpamba and Airtel Money for instant mobile wallet deductions.

Card Payments (Coming Soon): Visa capabilities are actively under development to support international and credit card processing.

Refund & Protection Policies
⚠️ Escrow Protection: Funds held for Shops, Events, and Bookings are fully protected. If a vendor fails to deliver, an event is canceled, or a lodging check-in cannot be fulfilled, the customer can seamlessly request and receive a 100% refund.

⛔ Real Estate Exception: The Property Viewing Fee is strictly non-refundable. Because the system immediately surrenders proprietary data (the exact GPS coordinates, routing, and the agent's private contact details) the moment payment lands, this fee cannot be reversed.